headline: 3 Consumer Stocks with Warning Signs
summary: Consumer discretionary businesses are levered to the highs and lows of economic cycles. Thankfully for the industry, all signs are pointing up as discretionary stocks have gained 19.1% over the past six months, beating the S&P 500’s 14.1% return.
